threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

trid.file_type: Mac OS X Mach-O 64-bit Intel executable

exiftool.ObjectFlags: No undefs, Dyld link, Two level, Binds to weak, Random address

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This binary is a backdoor/RAT that establishes encrypted C2 communication using RC4. It daemonizes itself by forking and detaching from the terminal. It provides extensive remote control capabilities, including a remote interactive shell (via `create_zsh` which execs `/bin/zsh`), file upload/download/deletion, process listing and killing, and gathering system information. It stores its configuration in a suspicious, masqueraded path: `/Library/Caches/com.apple.safari.ck`.
